        "assistant": "# Token Tax\n\nA **token tax** is a fee automatically applied to transactions involving a cryptocurrency token, typically built directly into the token's smart contract. Whenever someone buys, sells, or transfers the token, a small percentage is deducted and redirected for various purposes.\n\n## How It Works\n\nThe tax is coded into the token contract itself, so it's automatically enforced on every applicable transaction. Common tax rates range from 1% to 10%, though some projects use higher rates.\n\n## Common Uses for Collected Taxes\n\n1. **Liquidity Pool Funding** – Tokens are added to decentralized exchange liquidity pools to improve trading stability.\n2. **Marketing Wallet** – Funds promotional and growth activities.\n3. **Reflections/Rewards** – Redistributed to existing holders, rewarding them for holding.\n4. **Burn Mechanism** – Tokens are sent to a dead wallet, reducing supply (deflationary effect).\n5. **Development Fund** – Supports ongoing project development.\n6. **Charity Wallet** – Some projects donate a portion to charitable causes.\n\n## Types of Token Taxes\n\n- **Buy Tax** – Applied when purchasing the token.\n- **Sell Tax** – Applied when selling (often higher to discourage dumping).\n- **Transfer Tax** – Applied when moving tokens between wallets.\n\n## Pros and Cons\n\n**Advantages:**\n- Provides sustainable funding for projects\n- Encourages long-term holding\n- Can stabilize liquidity automatically\n\n**Disadvantages:**\n- Reduces effective returns for traders\n- Can be exploited by bad actors (e.g., \"honeypot\" scams with extremely high or hidden sell taxes)\n- May discourage trading activity\n- Can complicate compatibility with some exchanges\n\n## Important Note\n\nToken taxes are different from **government taxes** on cryptocurrency gains. The latter refers to capital gains or income taxes you owe to tax authorities when trading or earning crypto.\n\nAlways check a token's contract and tax structure before investing—high or hidden taxes are a common red flag in scam tokens.",
